    "notice": {
      "intro": "Welcome to Transcendance — the foosball match management system for the 42 cohort. Here's how to use the site.",
      "sections": [
        {
          "title": "🏓 Playing a match",
          "body": "Join the queue from the \"Queue\" page. Choose your mode (Chill or Competitive), your format (1v1, 2v2 or Solo), then wait for an opponent. A notification will alert you when your match starts."
        },
        {
          "title": "🪙 Tokens",
          "body": "You earn tokens by playing and winning matches. You can use them to bet on other players' matches from the Bets page. Tokens won on bets are credited immediately."
        },
        {
          "title": "🏆 Tournaments",
          "body": "Tournaments are organised by the BDE. You can register alone (waiting list to form a team) or with a partner. The format is 2-player teams. The bracket is revealed at the tournament start."
        },
        {
          "title": "📊 ELO",
          "body": "ELO is your ranking score. It increases when you win and decreases when you lose. Chill mode matches don't affect ELO. 1v1 and 2v2 rankings are independent."
        },
        {
          "title": "📅 The Queue",
          "body": "From the Queue page, you can see ongoing and upcoming matches. The pencil icon on your slot lets you edit or cancel your match. You can also bet on others' matches by hovering over them."
        }
      ]
